window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>The haunting story of the mother of the Tudors, Elizabeth of York, wife to Henry VII. </p><p> Beautiful eldest daughter of Edward IV and Elizabeth Woodville - the White Queen - the young princess Elizabeth faces a conflict of loyalties between the red rose and the white. Forced into marriage with Henry VII, she must reconcile her slowly growing love for him with her loyalty to the House of York, and choose between her mother's rebellion and her husband's tyranny. Then she has to meet the Pretender, whose claim denies the House of Tudor itself. </p><p>Read by Sarah Feathers.</p>"; 
